<subSubSection pageId="189" pageNumber="190" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="189.[151,1437,510,1471]" pageId="189" pageNumber="190">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1158,1183]" pageId="189" pageNumber="190">Remarks.</emphasis>
This new species differs from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Santos &amp; Azevedo" authorityYear="2000" box="[687,796,1158,1183]" class="Insecta" family="Bethylidae" genus="Anisepyris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="189" pageNumber="190" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="similis">
<emphasis box="[687,796,1158,1183]" italics="true" pageId="189" pageNumber="190">A. similis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by having the antennal scrobe ecarinate; the posterior mesoscutellar sulcus absent; the metapostnotal-propodeal suture straight; the mesopleuron with the lower fovea not divided; the metasomal segments glabrous; the paramere wide and as long as the basiparamere; the basivolsella with a short apical excavation at the inner margin; the cuspis with the arms long; and the aedeagus with the apical portion slender, whereas 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Santos &amp; Azevedo" authorityYear="2000" box="[433,538,1302,1327]" class="Insecta" family="Bethylidae" genus="Anisepyris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="189" pageNumber="190" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="similis">
<emphasis box="[433,538,1302,1327]" italics="true" pageId="189" pageNumber="190">A. similis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has the antennal scrobe carinate; the posterior mesoscutellar sulcus present; the metapostnotal-propodeal suture convergent to the first metapostnotal carina; the mesopleuron with the lower fovea divided; the metasomal segments sparsely setose; the paramere slender and shorter than the basiparamere; the basivolsela with the inner margin angled; the cuspis with the arms very short; and the aedeagus with the apical portion wide and swollen.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
